<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-27 01:42 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> American Loses First-Round Fight  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SYDNEY, Australia (AP) -- American Kay Poe, who made the Olympic
team thanks to the kindness of her best friend, lost her
first-round flyweight match in taekwondo.
</P>
<P>
   In an upset, Poe, of Houston, lost 4-3 Wednesday (Tuesday night
EDT) to Hanne Hoegh Poulsen of Denmark.
</P>
<P>
   Poe led 3-1 after two rounds before getting outscored 4-0 in the
final period. Poulsen had one point deducted to finish with the
one-point victory.
</P>
<P>
   ''I was much more cautious today than usual,'' Poe said. ''I'm
usually very aggressive, but today I just didn't play my game.''
</P>
<P>
   Poe's chances to win even a bronze medal ended later in the day
when Poulsen lost to Australia's Lauren Burns, eliminating Poulsen
from the final.
</P>
<P>
   Poe would have had a chance for bronze if Poulsen had reached
the final.
</P>
<P>
   Poe entered the Olympic trials in May ranked No. 1 in the world
in the flyweight class and destined for Sydney. But she dislocated
a kneecap in the semifinals, leaving her unable to compete in the
finals against her best friend, Esther Kim.
</P>
<P>
   Kim, who would have been an underdog if Poe had been healthy,
decided to give up her chance to make the team by forfeiting the
match to Poe.
</P>
<P>
   ''She did her best, the best that she could do today,'' said
Kim, who watched the bout from the stands, often yelling
encouragement to her friend.
</P>
<P>
   ''We are all proud of her,'' Kim said. ''She hasn't let anyone
down.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-09-27-00 0142 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
