<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-27 01:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Man found guilty of beating death  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   MALONE, N.Y. (AP) - A jury has found David P. Delosh guilty of
beating a 66-year-old man to death with a tire iron.
</P>
<P>
   Delosh was found guilty of two counts of first-degree murder as
well as first-degree attempted murder. It took the nine-woman,
three-man Franklin County jury a little more than 3 hours on
Tuesday to reach its verdict.
</P>
<P>
   Delosh will be sentenced Nov. 13. Judge Robert G. Main Jr. said
he will sentence Delosh's accomplice, Steven Trimm - who testified
against him - the same day.
</P>
<P>
   In a deal made with the Franklin County District Attorney's
Office, Trimm will receive 20 years to life in prison.
</P>
<P>
   Zerella was beaten to death with a tire iron in the driveway of
his Fort Covington home near the Canadian border, on Aug. 10, 1999.
He died of massive head injuries. Delosh and Trimm had gone to the
Zerella house that evening so Delosh could confront Diana Zerella's
boyfriend, Tony Russell.
</P>
<P>
   Delosh believed Russell - who is his brother-in-law - had turned
his family in for welfare fraud and had made an anonymous call to
his parole officer about his continued drinking and drug use.
</P>
<P>
   Those reports would've caused Delosh to be in violation of his
parole, and he would be sent back to prison.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
