<HEADLINE> Pleasantville man sentenced to 14 years for killing 4-year-old  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   MAYS LANDING, N.J. (AP) - A Pleasantville man who beat his
girlfriend's 4-year-old son to death, then helped her hide the body
has been sentenced to 14 years in prison.
</P>
<P>
   Antwan Dixon, 23, ''has the character flaw of callousness,''
First Assistant Prosecutor Murray Talasnik told state Superior
Court Judge Albert Garofolo on Sept. 21.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutors say Dixon was baby-sitting Nico Lloyd on June 12,
1999, while his mother worked in an Atlantic City casino when he
punched the boy three or four times, knocking him backward and
causing his head to hit a bed frame.
</P>
<P>
   When his mother, Altovise Lloyd, returned home, Dixon told her
the boy had fallen and was hurt, Talasnik said. Neither his mother
nor Dixon sought medical help for him and he died between that
afternoon and the next morning.
</P>
<P>
   His mother and Dixon wrapped the boy's body in a sheet, put him
in a black plastic garbage bag and hid him in the attic of the
Pleasantville apartment they shared.
</P>
<P>
   The body was found a week later when a landlord went searching
for the source of what neighbors said was a foul odor.
</P>
<P>
   Dixon was charged with murder, evidence tampering, conspiracy
and hindering apprehension in the boy's death.
</P>
<P>
   Altovise Lloyd, 20, was sentenced to up to five years in prison
in February for her part in hiding the body. She had pleaded guilty
to child endangerment and evidence tampering.
</P>
<P>
   Lloyd agreed to testify against Dixon as part of her plea
agreement.
</P>
</TEXT>
