<HEADLINE> WWF's The Rock To Star in Movie  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The Rock has struck gold.
</P>
<P>
   The World Wrestling Federation champ has signed a $5.5 million
deal with Universal Pictures to star as the action hero in ''The
Scorpion King,'' a spinoff of the upcoming ''The Mummy 2.'' It is
one of the highest amounts paid an actor in his first starring
role.
</P>
<P>
   The Rock, whose real name is Dwayne Johnson, had a small role as
the Scorpion King in ''The Mummy 2,'' in which his formerly
virtuous character becomes evil.
</P>
<P>
   ''When we watched the Rock in dailies of 'The Mummy 2,' his
charisma jumped out at us and we created a story that has a
prehistory context, adventure and humor,'' said Universal president
Kevin Misher. ''It's a terrific template for the birth of an action
hero.''
</P>
<P>
   ''The Mummy 2'' will be released in May, and ''The Scorpion
King'' is expected to hit theaters around Christmas 2001 or summer
2002.
</P>
</TEXT>
