<HEADLINE> 'T-Boz' Won't Tour With TLC  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Tionne ''T-Boz'' Watkins, a member of the
Grammy-winning R&AMP;B group TLC, says she won't be touring with the
group anymore because of health concerns.
</P>
<P>
   Watkins, who is pregnant, has been hospitalized several times
for the blood disease sickle cell anemia.
</P>
<P>
   She made the decision to stop touring after the all-girl group
did a pay-per-view special at the end of its last tour. She went
directly from a hospital to the stage and barely got through the
performance, she said.
</P>
<P>
   Touring was ''not healthy, not good and not smart,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   Watkins, an effervescent bleached blonde, wrote the single ''My
Getaway'' for the upcoming movie ''Rugrats In Paris.'' The movie is
to hit theaters in November.
</P>
