<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-27 16:05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Game which had $100 million jackpot in '99 will reappear  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) - A state Lottery game which generated a $100
million jackpot in 1999 is returning next month.
</P>
<P>
   Ticket sales will begin Sunday for a new Millennium Million
jackpot, state Lottery Director Margaret DeFrancisco said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The drawing for a starting jackpot of $50 million will be held
Oct. 21. If there is no grand prize winner, another drawing would
be held weekly starting Oct. 28 until someone hits the jackpot. New
tickets must be purchased for each drawing, DeFrancisco said.
</P>
<P>
   Tickets to the game sold well in 1999 and short-order cook
Johnnie Ely from the South Bronx collected $100 million for being
the sole jackpot winner.
</P>
<P>
   Players must select five numbers from 1 to 50 and one additional
number from a field of 1 to 25, called the Millennium Ball. Tickets
cost $2 per play.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
