<HEADLINE> Dow, Nasdaq, S&AMP;P All End Down  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   (New York-AP) -- The major averages slumped again as investors
concerned about third-quarter results punished the shares of poor
performers. After moving in and out of positive territory, the Dow
Jones industrial average ended down almost three points at 10,628.
But the broader market was higher as advancing issues topped losers
15 to 13, with about 1.1 billion shares changing hands on the New
York Stock Exchange. The technology-weighted Nasdaq composite saw
the most weakness, closing down 32 points, or nearly 1 percent, to
end at 3,656. The S &AMP; P 500 was down a fraction at 1,426.
</P>
<P>
   A round of bargain hunting early in the day helped push some
issues higher, but the rebound did not hold. The lack of staying
power was not a surprise as many big name stocks have spent much of
this month in a decline, reflecting uncertainty about how the
moderating economy will affect corporate profits.

</P>
