<HEADLINE> Drug companies gave $800,000 to GOP last month  </HEADLINE>
By JONATHAN D. SALANT
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) - The pharmaceutical industry gave more than
$800,000 to Republican Party committees last month after the Senate
voted to allow reimports of lower-priced U.S.-made drugs -
something the companies oppose.
</P>
<P>
