<HEADLINE> 'Big Brother' Down to Three Guys  </HEADLINE>
By FRAZIER MOORE
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Seattle beauty queen Jamie got the boot from
''Big Brother'' Wednesday, leaving three guys to run the house
until Friday's finale of the CBS reality series.
</P>
<P>
   ''This is cool!'' Curtis crowed after Jamie was ousted by a
phone-in viewer poll. ''We're making it to the last day.''
</P>
<P>
   Tough guy Eddie, a college student; easygoing law clerk Curtis;
and hunky Josh, also a student, are all that remains of the 10
original contestants -- five men and five women -- who moved into
CBS's microphone-and-camera-filled house on July 4.
</P>
<P>
   One will leave during Friday's finale with the $500,000 grand
prize. That choice, too, will be made by a phone poll.
</P>
<P>
   ''Oh, wow, it's been tense all day,'' Jamie told ''Big Brother''
host Julie Chen during the traditional post-eviction interview.
</P>
<P>
   Chen asked her why, with three attractive guys in close range,
were there ''no sparks''?
</P>
<P>
   ''I'm very, very single at the moment,'' she replied.
</P>
<P>
   A six-nights-a-week series since July 5, ''Big Brother'' has
played peeping Tom on the shrinking population sequestered in the
house near Los Angeles. Viewers have followed -- and played a role
in -- the elimination process leading up to Friday's finale.
</P>
<P>
   But the audience hasn't been what CBS had hoped for with ''Big
Brother,'' thanks to its general lack of sparks -- romantic,
dramatic or otherwise.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
