<HEADLINE> Fired employee pleads guilty to killing boss  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) - A fired employee admitted his guilt
Wednesday in the bludgeoning and stabbing death of his boss at an
electrical supply store.
</P>
<P>
   Kelvin Owes, 33, pleaded guilty to first-degree and
second-degree murder in return for life imprisonment without
possible of parole. Sentencing was set for Oct. 11 in Monroe County
Court.
</P>
<P>
   If Owes had been convicted at trial, he could have drawn a death
sentence.
</P>
<P>
   Owes has apparently been hiding in the loft of Maynard's
Electricap Supply Inc. in a commercial strip near the suburb of
Irondequoit. overnight, waiting to confront his boss. But the first
person to show up for work Feb. 21 was office manager Janet Welch.
</P>
<P>
   Welch, 53, was battered repeatedly around the head and body with
a blunt instrument and then stabbed multiple times in the torso and
throat with an unidentified edged weapon, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Police found Owes hiding in the rafters.
</P>
<P>
   Owes previously had served time for unlawful imprisonment and
criminal trespass and was placed on five years' probation.
</P>
<P>
   Welch, who was married, had worked at Maynard's for about 20
years.
</P>
</TEXT>
